{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":4801,"record_hash":"sha256:140b4bfdd6d0560e7360125a00ba5789f764723f09ad2731f55b38d76184e553","timestamp":"2026-05-21T05:42:06.457Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings against `226cf0fb` only.\\n\\n1. **Duplicate GitMeta hydration in `skim` path.**  \\n   `cli.rs:347-356` finds related sessions, `read.rs:244-262` builds `RelatedSession`, and `session_outline.rs:56-74` already walks turn details plus scans transcript previews at `session_outline.rs:214-228`. Then `skim.rs:134-167` calls `get_session_timeline_outline(..., None)` per session, which rereads summaries/details/transcript at `timeline_outline.rs:69-118`. That makes `skim::report` a second GitMeta reader, not a formatter, and explains cold-cache slowness.\\n\\n2. **Validation order is surprising for malformed `skim`.**  \\n   `cli.rs:342-349` resolves the repo before `skim::resolve_target()` validates target/value shape at `skim.rs:367-379`. So `but agentlog skim branch` outside a repo reports “No git repository found” instead of “branch target value is required.” Syntax errors should win before repo discovery.\\n\\n3. **Default target discovery shells out to the CLI from inside agentlog.**  \\n   `skim.rs:398-417` runs `but -C <workdir> --json status` and parses status JSON just to discover the applied branch. That leaks `but status` CLI/schema concerns into the agentlog read path, depends on whatever `but` is on `PATH`, and makes `but agentlog skim` recursively call a separate GitButler binary instead of using an internal boundary.\\n\\n4. **Review target UX leaks storage keys.**  \\n   The skill advertises `skim review <review-id-or-pull-request-key>` at `skill/SKILL.md:26-30`, and CLI normalization accepts raw `pull-request:` keys at `cli.rs:522-528`. But PR-only observed reviews are stored as `pull-request:{branch_key}#{pull_request}` in `environment.rs:306-318`. So `skim review 123` won’t find a PR-only review; the agent has to know the GitMeta-shaped branch-key-qualified key. That’s the wrong boundary showing through.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T05:42:06.457Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}